Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.42,0:00:03.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們的總統不僅服用精神藥物\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}We have a president who not only took mind-altering medication --
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.92,0:00:06.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,當美國艦隊與中國對峙時\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}a man who has his finger on the button
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.06,0:00:08.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他可以隨時批准實施打擊\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}while U.S. Ships are squaring off with China --
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.51,0:00:11.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,還授意他的白宮顧問去干預...\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}but then instructed his White House counsel to coach a --
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.76,0:00:13.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,據稱  先生  沒有被證實\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}Allegedly, sir. Not proven.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.59,0:00:17.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去干預證人  他的做法\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}To coach a witness. Which is behavior either resulting
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.92,0:00:19.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要麼是受藥物影響  要麼更糟\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}from the use of those drugs, or worse,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.52,0:00:21.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是有意想踐踏法律\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}a deliberate attempt to obstruct the law.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.78,0:00:24.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不覺得兩種情況都該被彈劾嗎\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}Now wouldn't you call either scenario impeachable?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.74,0:00:27.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那該由國會決定  先生  而不是我\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}That's for the United States Congress to decide, sir. Not me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.31,0:00:30.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道總統在服用任何藥物嗎\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}Were you aware that the president was taking any form of medication?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.34,0:00:31.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  我不知道\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}No, I was not.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.62,0:00:33.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你注意到他舉止古怪嗎\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}Did you notice him acting in a bizarre fashion?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.72,0:00:35.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-情緒不穩  語無倫次    -沒有  先生\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}- Unstable, incoherent?   - No, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.91,0:00:38.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-有任何奇怪的行為嗎    -沒有  先生\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}- Any odd behavior?   - No, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.25,0:00:41.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在貿易戰之際解僱幕僚長不算嗎\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}Not even firing his chief of staff in the midst of a trade war?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.53,0:00:44.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他沒有解僱我  是我主動辭職的\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}He didn't fire me. I resigned.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.02,0:00:45.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你能告訴我們為什麼嗎\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}Would you tell us why?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.37,0:00:49.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我辭職是因為我覺得自己無法\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}I resigned because I felt I could no longer
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.39,0:00:51.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再以最好的狀態為總統服務\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}serve the president to the best of my ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.78,0:00:54.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,發生了什麼變化  是什麼讓你得出那樣的結論\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}And what changed? How did you come to that conclusion?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.20,0:00:59.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我與白宮中的某些人\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}I had some fundamental differences of opinion
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.29,0:01:01.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,基本理念不合\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}with certain people in the White House.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.36,0:01:02.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,比如誰  總統嗎\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}Like who? The president?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.68,0:01:04.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  先生\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}No, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.05,0:01:05.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那某些人是指誰\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}Well, what certain people then?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.43,0:01:07.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,實際上只有一個人\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}One person, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.66,0:01:10.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,副總統  弗蘭克·安德伍德\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}The vice president, Frank Underwood.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.09,0:01:11.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他想讓你離開嗎\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}He wanted you gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.92,0:01:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不敢說副總統想怎麼樣  不想怎麼樣\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}I can't speak as to what the vice president did or didn't want.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.00,0:01:17.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他想要隱藏什麼嗎\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}Was he trying to hide anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.81,0:01:20.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是不是怕你曝光什麼\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}Was he afraid you might expose something?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.48,0:01:21.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那你得去問他  先生\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}You'd have to ask him, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.30,0:01:25.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,司法委員會正在上演的是一出鬧劇\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}What's happening in the Judiciary Committee is a farce.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.16,0:01:26.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,共和黨正在利用這種...\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}The Republicans are exploiting the situ--
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.89,0:01:28.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,插一句  副總統先生\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}Excuse me, Mr. Vice President,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.94,0:01:31.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不僅僅是共和黨\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}but it's not just Republicans.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.07,0:01:33.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不少民主黨人也站出來說\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}A number of Democrats have come out saying
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.51,0:01:35.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他們支援彈劾\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}they would support impeachment.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.52,0:01:37.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,包括多數黨黨鞭  傑姬·夏普\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}Including the Majority Whip, Jackie Sharp.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.81,0:01:39.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這令人髮指\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}Which is egregious,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.25,0:01:41.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因為委員會還在進行聽證\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}since the committee hasn't stopped hearing testimony,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.46,0:01:44.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,特別檢查官也沒有完成調查\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}and nor has the special prosecutor completed her investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.53,0:01:46.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你極力維護總統\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}You vigorously defend the president,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.77,0:01:48.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但有報道稱你們已經鬧僵\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}but there are reports that you've had a falling out.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.93,0:01:50.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你們好幾個星期沒說過話了\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}That you haven't spoken in weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.66,0:01:52.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一派胡言\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}That is simply not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.14,0:01:54.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我與白宮的高階官員通過話\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}I've spoken to senior staff at the White House
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.71,0:01:59.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他說總統擔心你會在2016年大選中與他競爭\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}who say the president is worried you want to run against him in 2016.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.05,0:02:01.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而就在今天  琳達·瓦斯奎茲暗指你...\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}And just today Linda Vasquez intimated that you --
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.66,0:02:04.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我相信總統一定會在2016年競選連任\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}Look, I fully expect that the president will run in 2016,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.99,0:02:07.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且我希望他能夠慷慨地邀請我\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}and I hope he's generous enough to invite me
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.15,0:02:08.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,作他的競選夥伴\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}to be his running mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.44,0:02:11.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,彈劾  定罪  如果是這個結果呢\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}Impeachment, conviction. Let's say it happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.10,0:02:13.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不會的  他完全是無辜的\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}It won't. He's completely innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.07,0:02:15.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們假設一下  你成了總統\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}Let's say it does happen. You become president.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.19,0:02:17.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不會去想像那個情形\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}That is not a scenario I'm going to entertain.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.10,0:02:19.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但你腦中肯定有過這個想法\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}But the thought must have crossed your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.34,0:02:21.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且可以說  如果不是因為你\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}And one could make the argument that the president
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.84,0:02:25.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,總統也不會陷入這樣的窘境\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}wouldn't be in this predicament if it weren't for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.00,0:02:28.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是你的幕僚長與馮和拉尼根的牽連\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}It's your staff's involvement with Feng and Lanagin
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.00,0:02:30.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,才引發了鄧巴的調查\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}that expanded Dunbar's investigation,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.16,0:02:32.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,這些彈劾聽證\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}Look, these impeachment hearings
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.47,0:02:33.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}隨之發現了出行記錄\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}which resulted in the travel logs --
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.40,0:02:34.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是政治操縱的結果\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}are the result of political maneuvering,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.39,0:02:37.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-而不是    -是你在操縱還是共和黨\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}- not the fact that--   - Your maneuverings, or the Republicans?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.51,0:02:39.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,莫里  我一直很喜歡你\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}Morley, I've always liked you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.70,0:02:40.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的問題很尖銳\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}You ask the tough questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.00,0:02:43.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你當然可以質疑我的判斷\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}And you can certainly question my judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.35,0:02:45.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但不要質疑我的愛國心\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}But do not question my patriotism.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.87,0:02:49.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我為國家和總統服務  而不是我自己\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}I serve this nation and my president, not myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.81,0:02:51.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他滿口謊言\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}He's lying through his teeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.02,0:02:52.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們所做的已經見效了\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}What we're doing is working.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.95,0:02:55.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,讓大家一直私下談論\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}We keep the whisper campaign alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.08,0:02:57.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們讓他顯得渴望權利  顯得奸詐\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}We spin him as power-hungry, as duplicitous.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.75,0:02:59.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,將焦點集中在他身上  而不是你\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}Focus attention on him. Not you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.50,0:03:01.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最新支援率是多少  20%嗎\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}What's the latest? 20%?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.17,0:03:04.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,佐格比的資料是24%  你的講話起了作用\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}Zogby has you at 24. Your speech made a difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.51,0:03:07.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,支援率正在上升\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}The approval numbers are moving in the right direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.04,0:03:11.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們不能再這麼小打小鬧了\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}We need to do more than play the spin game.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.32,0:03:16.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我們要打垮弗蘭克  讓他而不是我去當犧牲品\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}We need to destroy Frank. Offer his head instead of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.39,0:03:20.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-我們利用雷蒙德·塔斯克    -怎麼利用\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}- We use Raymond Tusk.   - How?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.96,0:03:24.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在他的聽證會上  在他去司法委員會時\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}At his hearing. When he goes to the Judiciary.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.44,0:03:27.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,先生  你已經被指控干預一個證人了\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}Sir, you're already being accused of coaching one witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.92,0:03:28.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你再干預另一...\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}If you take steps to coach anoth--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.74,0:03:30.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是干預  是讓他說出事實\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}Not coaching. The truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.23,0:03:32.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,雷蒙德承認洗錢\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}Raymond admits to the money laundering,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.94,0:03:36.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把弗蘭克推到風口浪尖  說我什麼都不知道\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}puts Frank at the center of this, and says I knew nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.24,0:03:38.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,之後我們會回報他的誠實\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}And then we'll reward him for his honesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.92,0:03:40.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是說特赦嗎\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}You mean a pardon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.57,0:03:45.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想讓你跟他去談\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}I want you to talk to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.43,0:03:47.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,讓我自己陷於危險之中嗎\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}And put myself at risk?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.16,0:03:49.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你現在不在政府供職了\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}Well, you're not part of this administration anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.57,0:03:52.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沒有法律規定你不能去拜訪雷蒙德·塔斯克\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}There's no law that says you can't pay Raymond Tusk a visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.88,0:03:57.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,作為回報  辭職也不非得永久有效  琳達\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}And in return, resignations don't have to last forever, Linda.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.28,0:04:05.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果我這麼做  你得和我保持距離  越遠越好\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}If I do this, you have to be a million miles away.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.16,0:04:08.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,特莉莎和我會去戴維營\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}Tricia and I'll go to Camp David.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.04,0:04:12.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不算特別遠  但夠了\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}It's not a million miles away, but it'll do the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.50,0:04:15.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我可以對琳達下手  調查她的過去\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}I can go after Linda. Dig into her past --
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.48,0:04:18.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,搞定她解決不了大問題\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}Neutralizing her won't neutralize the bigger problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.12,0:04:20.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是總統想要我的命\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}It's the president that's after blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.56,0:04:21.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那他打算怎麼做\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}Then what's his move?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.58,0:04:24.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他不能要求我辭職  只能把我擠走\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}He can't ask me to resign. He'd have to force me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.46,0:04:28.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要擠走我的話  如果我是他\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}And to do that, if I were him,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.77,0:04:32.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,肯定會回去找最初成就我的人\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}I would return to the hand that first fed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.61,0:04:34.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-雷蒙德·塔斯克嗎    -沒錯\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}- Raymond Tusk?   - Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.88,0:04:37.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不會  他要是把你捲進去  他自己也難保\N{\fn微軟雅黑\fs14}No, he'd have to implicate himself to implicate you.
